<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-03-16T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-03-16T20:00:00-05:00" n="241" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d241">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94 Advisory Committee/23:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Switzerland (<persName type="to">Wilson</persName>),
                                at Geneva</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-03-16T20:00:00-05:00">March 16, 1933—8
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>89. Department’s telegrams 85, March 11, 7 p.m., and 86, March 11, 8
                                p.m.,<note n="68" xml:id="d241fn68">For telegram No. 86, see <ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_117"><hi rend="italic">Foreign
                                        Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 117</ref>.</note> and your telegram 150, March
                            15, 8 p.m.</p>
                        <p>For guidance:</p>
                        <p>The Department desires that you do not participate in conversations which
                            may take place in connection with the examination of “problems of the
                            export of arms in relation to the present situation in the Far East”
                            other than, if asked, to state the attitude and policy of this
                            Government as set forth in the pertinent sections of Department’s 85,
                            March 11, 7 p.m.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
